                  <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">

                     <Heading>Abstract.</Heading>

                     <Para> In this paper we obtain a new version of stability of matter, which in particular shows that Thomas-Fermi theory is asymptotically correct in the limit of large nuclear charges uniformly in the number of nuclei. As a consequence we give a new lower bound on the volume of matter with an improved dependence on the nuclear charges.</Para>

                  </Abstract>

